abstract: A federal judge spoke at Stanford Law School. Chaos ensued.
snippet: A federal judge spoke at Stanford Law School. Chaos ensued.
lead_paragraph: Stuart Kyle Duncan — a federal appeals court judge appointed by Donald Trump — visited Stanford Law School this month to give a talk. It didn’t go well.

abstract: Moldova, like its neighbor Ukraine, wants closer relations with the West but has long battled Russian political interference and intimidation.
snippet: Moldova, like its neighbor Ukraine, wants closer relations with the West but has long battled Russian political interference and intimidation.
lead_paragraph: The Biden administration on Wednesday imposed sanctions on more than 20 Moldovan and Russian individuals and entities for assisting Russian efforts to manipulate Moldova’s political system.

main: New U.S. sanctions target Russian efforts to manipulate the politics in Moldova, a neighbor of Ukraine.
print_headline: U.S. Sanctions Take Aim At Meddling in Moldova

abstract: Ties to potentially coercive labor practices could prove a problem for an industry that is heavily dependent on China, once a new law barring Xinjiang products goes into effect.
snippet: Ties to potentially coercive labor practices could prove a problem for an industry that is heavily dependent on China, once a new law barring Xinjiang products goes into effect.
lead_paragraph: The photograph on the mining conglomerate’s social media account showed 70 ethnic Uyghur workers standing at attention under the flag of the People’s Republic of China. It was March 2020 and the recruits would soon undergo training in management, etiquette and “loving the party and the country,” their new employer, the Xinjiang Nonferrous Metal Industry Group, announced.

main: Red Flags for Forced Labor Found in China’s Car Battery Supply Chain
print_headline: U.S. Rule Risks Disrupting Global Battery Supply

abstract: A pioneer in radio art and, later internet art, she created a blend of synthesizer compositions and found sounds that opened new artistic terrain.
snippet: A pioneer in radio art and, later internet art, she created a blend of synthesizer compositions and found sounds that opened new artistic terrain.
lead_paragraph: Helen Thorington, whose haunting sonic compositions helped bring the medium of radio art to a national audience and provided the soundscape for filmmakers, artists and choreographers, died on April 13 in Lincoln, Mass. She was 94.

main: Helen Thorington, Who Brought Sonic Art to the Airwaves, Dies at 94
print_headline: Helen Thorington, 94; Brought Sonic Art to Airwaves

abstract: The comparison to Stalin’s decision to let millions in Ukraine starve represents one of the pope’s strongest condemnations yet of the Russian invasion.
snippet: The comparison to Stalin’s decision to let millions in Ukraine starve represents one of the pope’s strongest condemnations yet of the Russian invasion.
lead_paragraph: Pope Francis on Wednesday compared the war in Ukraine to the “terrible Holodomor genocide” of the 1930s, when the policies of the Soviet dictator, Joseph Stalin, caused a devastating famine in Ukraine.

main: Pope Francis compares Russia’s war against Ukraine to a devastating Stalin-era famine.

abstract: Black Entertainment Television made the first Black billionaire in the United States. Will a Black executive buy it back?
snippet: Black Entertainment Television made the first Black billionaire in the United States. Will a Black executive buy it back?
lead_paragraph: When the cable giant Viacom bought Black Entertainment Television at the turn of the millennium for $2.34 billion, it made Robert L. Johnson, BET’s founder, the first Black billionaire in the United States.

main: Third Black-Owned Company Emerges as Suitor for BET

abstract: I prefer to think of the winter solstice not as the shortest day of the year but as the longest night.
snippet: I prefer to think of the winter solstice not as the shortest day of the year but as the longest night.
lead_paragraph: NASHVILLE — This year the winter solstice arrives on Dec. 21 in the shank of the dark afternoon. Officially the first day of astronomical winter, the solstice is better known as the shortest day of the year. I prefer to think of it as the longest night of the year, for I am making friends with darkness.

main: Falling a Little Bit in Love With the Dark
print_headline: Falling a Little Bit in Love With the Dark

abstract: The swift advance of artificial intelligence in politics is already blurring the boundaries between fact and fake.
snippet: The swift advance of artificial intelligence in politics is already blurring the boundaries between fact and fake.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic Party has begun testing the use of artificial intelligence to write first drafts of some fund-raising messages, appeals that often perform better than those written entirely by human beings.
